<br>
It is my understanding that after the 85-95 Con a Troll has at level 50 (variation for the 10 points either added or not at level 1), every additional 6 points of Con from items (up to +75) and buffs (+47 base and +69 spec) grants Skalds 20 hp.<br>
<br>
So a SC, max buffed Skald has 95+75+47+69 or 286 Con. This is approximately a 648 hp increase (if my math and theory of it being 20 hp per 6 Con). Add in +200 hits from items that is a 848 hp increase.<br>
<br>
My questions are:<br>
<br>
whether my theory (20 hits per 6 Con) is correct.<br>
<br>
whether there is an upper cap for Skald hp (i.e. like 1800)<br>
<br>
and whether an 848 hp increase (if correct) reaches that cap. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amstellight>Amstel Light</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/19/03 9:59:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=514.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HP Cap</span><hr size=1> Its definitely not an 1800 cap, I break 1800 hps all the time as kobold skald.<br>
